    newsArticle3Date: "January 7, 2026",
    newsArticle3Category: "Professional Law",
    newsArticle3Subtitle: "StBVV Amendment as of 01.07.2025 and Fee Agreements",
    newsArticle3Text1: "The Tax Advisor Fee Regulation governs fee frameworks and billing systems; adjustments come into effect on 01.07.2025. At the same time, it remains possible to deviate through a fee agreement and agree to higher fees – but only with proper formal design.",
    newsArticle3Text2: "Text form (§ 126b BGB) is important in practice so that agreements are effective and billing-safe. A clear mandate and fee structure strengthens transparency, reduces conflicts and supports a professional firm image.",
    newsArticle3Text3: "For clients, this means: Fee agreements must be clearly formulated and documented to prevent later disputes. Tax advisors should communicate their fee structure early and design it transparently so that clients know which services are billed at what level.",
    newsArticle3CTATitle: "Do you have questions about the new fee regulations?",
