    newsArticle4Title: "Bogus Self-Employment with 1-Person UG/GmbH",
    newsArticle4Date: "December 31, 2025",
    newsArticle4Category: "Social Insurance",
    newsArticle4Subtitle: "1-Person UG/GmbH as Contractor: No \"Free Pass\"",
    newsArticle4Text1: "Engaging a 1-person UG/GmbH does not automatically prevent bogus self-employment if the shareholder-managing director actually works like an employee. The actual circumstances remain decisive: integration, instructions, entrepreneurial risk, external appearance.",
    newsArticle4Text2: "Especially with long-term, exclusive assignments in organizations, high risks arise. The status determination procedure (§ 7a SGB IV) is recommended to create legal certainty before starting the activity.",
    newsArticle4Section1Title: "Distinction Self-Employment vs. Employment",
    newsArticle4Section1Text1: "Status distinction is increasingly handled strictly by case law because actual integration and dependence on instructions are heavily weighted. Contracts alone do not protect if the lived practice acts like an employment relationship. The consequences are considerable: back-claiming of social insurance contributions and often also payroll tax risks.",
    newsArticle4Section1Text2: "Companies should therefore check project-based assignments, instruction structures and documentation early. Particularly critical are constellations where the shareholder-managing director is firmly integrated into the organization, has regular working hours and has little entrepreneurial freedom of decision.",
    newsArticle4CTATitle: "Unclear status questions? We help with legally secure design.",
